╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝

 New in v10:

   M-1  CFG table indirection
        Real config stored under a random per-session getgenv key.
        The local `CFG` variable is a __index/__newindex proxy — external
        environment scanners see an opaque empty table, not NCBCFG with
        known fields.  The loaded-guard key is also randomised.

   M-2  Function identity concealment
        Core functions (filter chain, WireCharacter, FindRemote, DragAndFire)
        wrapped in newcclosure after definition.  Each session produces
        unique bytecode hashes; static fingerprint databases get no match.
        Graceful fallback when newcclosure is unavailable.

   M-3  Upvalue scrubbing on kill
        When P is pressed, all sensitive cache tables are cleared in-place
        (table.clear) before the GC pass.  The config's sensitive fields are
        also zeroed.  Both session getgenv keys are deleted.  Post-kill env
        inspection finds nothing meaningful.

   M-5  Lazy-load getconnections
        SuppressSignal / RestoreSignal no longer exist at module level.
        getconnections is resolved inside DragAndFire's task.spawn only —
        the function is referenced in the environment for ≤ LerpFrames×(1/60)
        seconds per drag, then discarded.

   R-3  Signal suppression window minimisation
        Suppress/restore now bracket only the single `torso.CFrame = write`
        per lerp frame, not the entire loop.  CFrame-change signal gaps
        detectable in server logs are reduced from ~LerpFrames×(1/60) s
        to a single-tick window per frame (~1/500 s with pcall overhead).

   D-3  GUI absence mode
        The C keybind now fully destroys the ScreenGui instance rather than
        hiding it.  Re-pressing C calls BuildGUI() from scratch.  The gui
        name is randomised on each build — no fixed string in CoreGui's
        child list between sessions.

   D-4  Arc part existence minimisation
        Two sub-features:
          • Part names randomised on each BuildArcVis call (replaces the
            fixed "_NCBArc" string that string-based scanners keyed on).
          • CFG.ArcHideStill (default true): arc parts are destroyed and
            creation is skipped when the local character's HumanoidRootPart
            velocity has been below 0.5 studs/s for 45+ consecutive frames
            (~0.75 s).  Parts don't exist while the player is standing still,
            which is both the highest detection-risk and lowest-utility window.
          • Arc parts are parented to the first Folder found in workspace, or
            to a new randomly-named Folder if none exists, rather than
            directly in workspace root.

   N-4  Idle remote-call suppression
        FindRemote is not probed and DragAndFire is not called when the
        script has been idle (no trigger active on a valid target) for more
        than IDLE_TIMEOUT seconds (default 60).  After idle, the first
        Heartbeat with a valid target resets the timer and probing resumes.
        Zero network traffic during idle periods.

   QoL-7  Keybind conflict detection
        On rebind, the new key is checked against all four existing keybinds
        (Toggle / ToggleVis / ToggleUI / Kill).  A conflict flashes the
        trigger chip and REBIND button amber, blocks the commit, and fires a
        notification naming the conflicting bind.  The rebind state is cleared
        automatically after 1.5 s.

